The paper focuses on developing a scalable video parsing and evaluation platform for large-scale surveillance videos, which involves processing and analyzing Big Visual Data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of advanced techniques for Big Data processing, such as Spark Streaming, Kafka, and Hadoop Distributed Filesystem (HDFS), which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the development of intelligent incremental algorithms to enhance the performance of various visual recognition tasks, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the evaluation of the system's performance, which could be related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
